news.title: Gurugram: Illegal structures in IAF ammo depot buffer zone razed
news.para: Officials said that five unauthorised under-construction residential buildings in the restricted area around the IAF ammunition depot, two unauthorised structures in Rajendra Park and one each in Surat Nagar and the Daultabad industrial area were demolished.

news.title: Oberoi Realty acquires 4.2-acre land parcel in Mumbai's Bhandup suburb
news.para: The transaction was concluded and registered by Oberoi Constructions on November 25. The developer has paid stamp duty worth Rs 5.96 crore to register the deal, showed documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm.

news.title: Telangana: Deccan Cements mining operations flouted green norms, says NGT
news.para: Deccan Cements Limited has allegedly violated environmental clearance conditions and mined limestone illegally in Suryapet district.

news.title: Large pharma companies increasingly buying land in Hyderabad
news.para: The Indian pharma industry has shown a double-digit growth of around 15% in 2021, led by the growth of Covid-19 products in the last one year, as against a single digit growth of 3% shown in 2020, according to Indian pharmaceutical market research company Pharmasofttech AWACS Pvt Ltd.

news.title: Housr ventures into rental homes business
news.para: Housr will be offering fully-furnished and managed 1,2 & 3 BHK apartments with rents starting at around Rs 25-30,000 per month for a single room.

news.title: Settl launches four co-living facilities in Gurugram
news.para: Settl is presently operating 1,200 beds and is plans to reach 3,000 operational beds by December 2022. The brand plans to provide 1,000 beds by the end of 2022 in Gurugram.

news.title: Indie Homefin, eight NBFCs surrender certificates of registration to RBI
news.para: The Mumbai-based Indie Homefin Pvt Ltd has surrendered the Certificate of Registration (CoR) granted by the National Housing Bank and the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has therefore cancelled the CoR, the central bank said in a statement on Thursday.

news.title: Germany's Adler Group seals second major property sale to cut debt
news.para: Adler Group, whose shares have crashed since it was targeted last year by short sellers critical of its business, said it would receive net cash proceeds of 600 million euros ($686 million) from the sale to private-equity firm KKR.

news.title: More Chinese developers seek to extend bond terms to avert default
news.para: The market is also watching the outcome of China Evergrande Group's meeting with onshore bondholders, as the voting period to approve an extension will end on Thursday. The firm has so far met payments on onshore bonds though it has defaulted on some offshore bonds.

news.title: Chinese developer Yuzhou Group offers bond swap to avert default
news.para: Yuzhou Group offered to extend by one year the maturity of two U.S. dollar bonds due this month in a filing late on Wednesday. It also said it expects a delay in coupon payments totalling $110 million that are due in January and February.

news.title: Developer Sunac China plans $580 million share sale to repay loans
news.para: The Hong Kong-listed developer plans to sell 452 million new shares, or 8.3% of the enlarged share capital, to controlling shareholder Sunac International Investment Holdings, it said in a filing to the Hong Kong bourse.

news.title: Germany asks banks to build buffers as property market heats up
news.para: Regulators cut extra buffer requirements to zero at the onset of the crisis but property prices soared on the back of record low rates and the market is now 10% to 30% overvalued, leaving lenders especially vulnerable to a price correction, the Bundesbank said earlier.

news.title: Jaipur: Sangam Tower, Moti Mahal Cinema sealed for not paying UD tax
news.para: Civil Lines zones deputy commissioner, Ramkishore Mehta, said Rs 23, 22,690 of urban development tax was due on Sangam Towers from April 1, 2017, to March 31, 2021, under the Rajasthan Municipal Development Corporation Tax Rules, 2007.

news.title: North Delhi civic body council rejects proposal to raise tax burden on residents
news.para: ​The North Delhi Municipal Corporation also decided not to approve the Commissioner's proposal to reduce rebate on property taxes by 5 per cent.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP razes 250 structures in 14 colonies, frees 46 acres
news.para: During the drive, the team in presence of police force razed around 250 structures, 16 under-construction houses, four shops, a property dealer's office, boundary walls and road networks.
